    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dating system based on the seasonal year of approximately 365 1/4 days, the time it takes the earth to revolve once around the sun. The Egyptians appear to have been the first to develop a solar calendar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
